  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b9a\u0baa\u0bc8 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b95 \u0b9a\u0bc1\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd : \u0b86\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0ba4\u0bae \u0b95\u0bca\u0bb1\u0b9f\u0bbe\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0b95 \u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0ba9 \u0bb0\u0ba3\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Susil as Chief Minister: Prasanna Ranatunga as Chief Whip of the ruling party",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "Also, Minister Prasanna Ranatunga has been re-appointed as the Chief Whip of the ruling party.",
        "The first parliamentary session will be held today after Ranil Wickremesinghe was sworn in as President.",
        "Minister Dines Gunawardena, who previously served as the Chief Minister, has been sworn in as the Prime Minister. Education Minister Sushil Premajayantha has been appointed to fill the vacant post of the council principal.",
        "Parliament will convene today, Wednesday at 10.00 am under the chairmanship of Speaker Mahinda Yappa Abeywardhana. The first event will be the swearing in of Vajira Abeyvarthana.",
        "While Ranil Wickramasinghe went to Parliament on the only National List seat available to the United National Party in the General Election, now that seat has become vacant as he has been elected to the post of President.",
        "According to the letter sent by the Election Commission to the Secretary of the United National Party, with the full approval of the Central Executive Committee and the Management Council of the United National Party, the name of the party's vice president Vajira Abeywardhana was submitted to the Election Commission by the party's secretary, Palitha Range Bandara.",
        "Based on that, the Election Commission had announced the name of Vajira Abeywardhana as a member of the National List of the United National Party for the vacant seat in the Parliament last week through the gazette.",
        "Based on that, when Parliament meets today, Vajira Abeywardhana will take oath as a Member of Parliament in the presence of the Speaker.",
        "During today's Parliament session, the state of emergency declared by the President under the Public Security Act will be debated till 4.30 pm.",
        "On the 17th, a state of emergency was declared during Ranil Wickramasinghe's tenure as Acting President through the announcement of Special Gazette No. 2288/30.",
        "According to the law, if the approval of the Parliament is not obtained within 14 days, the declaration of the state of emergency is null and void.",
        "This declaration was made in accordance with the power given to the President under the Public Security Ordinance to maintain the security of the people, the peace of the country, and the provision and services essential to public life."
      ],
